RBAC Components
______________________

	There are five main objects.

ServiceAccount / User
        │
        ▼
      Role
        │
        ▼
   RoleBinding

or

ServiceAccount / User
        │
        ▼
   ClusterRole
        │
        ▼
ClusterRoleBinding


_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Service account: it is identity used by the pod to authenticate with the kubernetes api server

	"ServiceAccount = Identity of a Pod."


ROLE: it defains the set of permission for the resource in an single namepsce 

	"Role = What actions are allowed in one namespace".
Example:

In the single/dev namespace:

	 Get Pods
	ist Pods
	Delete Pods

ROLE BINDING: This grants a permission which are mentioned in role  to the service account/user/group

	"ROLEBINDING = CONNECTING SERVICE ACCOUNT WITH ROLE"

CLUSTER ROLE: This will define the set of role that are applicable accross the cluster 

	"ClusterRole = Role for the entire cluster".
Example:

in entair cluster it Can:

	View Nodes
	View Namespaces
	View PersistentVolumes

These are cluster-scoped resources.


CLUSTER ROLE BINDING": This will grant set of permission which are defined in cluster role  to the user /group/service account accross the cluster
	

"clusterRoleBinding" = connecting cluster rol with service account/pod/user/gropu for entair cluster access"
	
